Lagos – Gernot Rohr, Super Eagles technical adviser, has described as a big joke allegation that he plans to name players who agrees that he would manage them for the World Cup. Speaking on SuperSport Monday Night Football, the coach said that having coached for 45 years, he could not get himself involved in sucha dastardly act. According to him, “My only job is to coach the Super Eagles. This is my 45th year in professional football. “The man who wrote that story has to be careful because if a lawyer should come he will close down the shop and will go to jail.” Rohr assured that only fit players would be selected for the World Cup. 0 comments